{
  "text": "In other words, what this lemma says is that on the line between any point w and the point w * , the surrogate loss functionF is convex from any point -even though it is not convex overall. This is akin to the restricted secant inequality condition described in [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . The following theorem uses this lemma to establish our first result: that in the noiseless setting with no outliers, w * is the only fixed point (in expectation) of MKL-SGD. ",
